<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-262-210  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 262 210.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  March 20 1990 v4 n11 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Drive vendor aims low in price war. (Hard Drives Internationalannounces aggressively priced Macintosh hard disks)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hard Drives International (prices).andO;Product:   Hard Drives International POWERDrive (Hard disk drive) (prices).andO;Topic:     Hard DiskDisk DrivesPrice Cutting.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Hard Drive International's price list. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PC disk supplier moves in on MacandM;By Henry NorrandM;Tempe, Ariz.andP;  -- Declaring &quot;The war is on!&quot; Hard Drives International thismonth announced cuts in what was already an aggressively priced line ofinternal and external drives.andM;HDI, which has seen its annual sales in the IBM PC and compatible world soarto almost $50 million in just four years, first laid claim to the title of&quot;low-price leader&quot; in the Macintosh storage market last fall with theintroduction of its POWERDrive series.andP;  The line features some of the loweststorage prices ever advertised for the Macintosh, including a 20-Mbyteinternal Seagate drive now priced at $269 and a 44-Mbyte SyQuestremovable-cartridge drive for $649.andM;Winner of several awards for services from PC-oriented publications, HDIprovides a 30-day guarantee, a one-year replacement policy, toll-free salesand support lines, and a promise that turnaround time on returns will notexceed 48 hours.andM;The standard external and internal drives ship with Disk Manager, Mac utilitysoftware from On-track Computer Systems Inc. of Eden Prairie, Minn.andP;  Featuresinclude software selection of SCSI ID; automatic and manual head parking; afull display of drive and format parameters; and hard partitioning (A/UXcompatible) with password protection, a desk-accessory mounter and anautomounting option.andM;For its SyQuest-based removable drive, however, an HDI spokes-woman said that&quot;because of the complexity of removable media, we have found it necessary toevaluate several software packages,&quot; and that it has not yet made a finalselection.andM;Hard Drives International is located at 1912 W. Fourth St., Tempe, Ariz.andO;85281; (602) 967-5128; (800) 234-3475.andO;</TEXT></DOC>